        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Daylight Saving Time doesnt work with dates over 2038 eg:  I create Zend_Date 05.05.2000 and set gmt time to 12:00. Then i switch timezone to 'Europe\/Warsaw' (Warsaw  is in summer in GMT+2, while normally in GMT+1), i get 14:00 - everything ok.\n\nBut when i do the same things with date 05.05.2040 i get 13:00 - (gmt offset +1h) - with is wrong. the sample code is placed below:\n\n{code}\n\tdate_default_timezone_set('Europe\/Warsaw');\n\t$date = new Zend_Date();\n\t$date->setTimezone('UTC');\n\t$date->set('25-05-2050 12:00:00');\n\techo $date->get('dd-MM-YYYY HH:mm:ss') . ' (' . $date->getTimezone() . ')<br>';\n\t$date->setTimezone('Europe\/Warsaw');\n\techo $date->get('dd-MM-YYYY HH:mm:ss') . ' (' . $date->getTimezone() . ')<br>';\n\t\n\t$date = new Zend_Date();\n\t$date->setTimezone('UTC');\n\t$date->set('25-05-2020 12:00:00');\n\techo $date->get('dd-MM-YYYY HH:mm:ss') . ' (' . $date->getTimezone() . ')<br>';\n\t$date->setTimezone('Europe\/Warsaw');\n\techo $date->get('dd-MM-YYYY HH:mm:ss') . ' (' . $date->getTimezone() . ')<br>';\n{code}\n\noutput for this code is: \n\n25-05-2050 12:00:00 (UTC)\n25-05-2050 13:00:00 (Europe\/Warsaw)\n25-05-2020 12:00:00 (UTC)\n25-05-2020 14:00:00 (Europe\/Warsaw)\n\nwhile it should be:\n\n25-05-2050 12:00:00 (UTC)\n25-05-2050 14:00:00 (Europe\/Warsaw)\n25-05-2020 12:00:00 (UTC)\n25-05-2020 14:00:00 (Europe\/Warsaw)\n"
        },
